ilence open like a door.\",\n        \"Synchronize with the aeolian harps and open the subchamber between notes without tripping the bell-scribes—match your breath to the court’s measured hush and turn the lock on a single shared heartbeat.\",\n        \"Mix a small vial of breath-tincture using Solace enzymes on-site—combine hoarded breath, echo-stone trace, and balm to bind the city’s average note into a portable cure.\",\n        \"Evade Ledger auditors led by Dorel Glassant and exit before the hour turns—leave no footprint in ink or dust, and let the harps remember only your silence.\"\n      ],\n      \"dialogue\": [\n        {\"speaker\": \"Ayo Solace\", \"lines\": \"I will not sanctify theft, Tallea, but I will sanctify a cure that gives our people steadier lungs and calmer nights. The Courts have bottled years of quarrel-breath under their floors, and the Ledger names it record while their clerks sip from it in secret to pace their predictions. If we draw no more than a healer’s cup and knead it with enzyme and echo, we return something stronger than we take, a tincture that steadies both law and lifeblood. You read the lulls like a midwife reads a pulse, and I can teach the mixture to hum at the city’s average rather than at any one faction’s shout. Walk with me at moon-tier, bring courage dry enough not to squeak, and let our tools speak softly enough that even the harps lean down to listen.\"},\n        {\"speaker\": \"Tallea Miranth\", \"lines\": \"Every time I step beneath those strings I taste the cold of my first mistake on the back of my teeth, and the Courts whisper all my promises back with perfect pitch. I will still go, because a cure that returns breath to those the Courts forget is a debt I am willing to carry in daylight. Rhyss Quell owes me a lull after the chain-pass audit, and he hates the taste of Ledger varnish as much as I do, though he drinks ritual for breakfast. If we are caught, we speak the plan aloud, and we speak it so clean the h