ds cannot be heard, counting heartbeats with your tongue pressed to your teeth so you do not hurry. Ayo folds enzyme into hoarded breath, her motions a liturgy of economy and grace, and you tilt the vial as if pouring a dawn back into its cloud. You do not speak, you only breathe with the Courts, trusting that the city will forgive the medicine because it never felt you take it. Your steps carry you to the far stair well before the bell-scribes even realize the wind had held its breath.\", \"outcome\": \"The lock turns like a note resolved, and the subchamber sighs as if relieved to be useful again, letting its chill brush your cheeks without alarming the harps. The tincture takes the glow of the Solace kit and the mild viscosity of echoed speech, and when you cork it the vial hums faintly with the city’s average grief and resolve. Dorel’s auditors arrive a blink late, finding nothing but the aftertaste of salt-clean air and a faint harmonic fingerprint in the hinges that only you would recognize. Rhyss shakes once and then laughs bitterly into his sleeve, already drafting a maintenance note that will pass every inspection and still tell the truth to those who can read its knots. You exit before the hour turns, carrying a medicine no witness can testify against because no witness knows it exists, and the Courts continue to sing with their usual iron grace.\"},\n        {\"id\": \"C3\", \"title\": \"Cut a Quiet Bond: Bargain a Window From the Ledger, Then Outpace It\", \"text\": \"You meet Dorel in a pocket where sound does not carry and talk about winds instead of laws until the price of an empty minute becomes clear. You offer him a harmless future: a chance to hear the city’s average, not its names, and the promise that no ledger will be fed tonight beyond the one already gorged on breath. He smiles like a cat who has learned the gate’s hinge song, and he gives you a window because the experiment might be useful even if it is not profitable yet. You accept with a 